# LegalOps — Environment Variables Reference
#
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in real values for local dev.
# In production: provision via secret manager (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets
# Manager, sealed-secrets, etc.) — never commit `.env`.
#
# All secrets here are required/optional per the table below. Keep `.env`
# permissions tight: `chmod 600 .env`.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED — pseudonymization salt (LGPD Art. 13)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used as HMAC-SHA256 key for the PII redactor placeholders + audit hashes of
# original PII values. Without a secret salt, hashes of CPF/CNPJ become
# brute-forceable (small numeric space) and pseudonymization is non-compliant.
#
# Minimum 16 bytes. Generate with: `openssl rand -hex 24`
# Subcommands that touch PII exit with code 2 when this is unset.
LEGALOPS_PII_SALT=replace-me-with-openssl-rand-hex-24-output

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL — defense-in-depth keys
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Audit log tamper-evidence. Without a key, the SHA-256 hash chain still
# detects accidental corruption, but an attacker who can rewrite the whole
# `audit_log` table can recompute valid hashes. With an HMAC key (kept out of
# the DB), full-table rewrite is computationally infeasible.
# Generate with: `openssl rand -hex 32`
# LEGALOPS_AUDIT_HMAC_KEY=

# SMTP password for the email notifier. Takes precedence over the TOML
# `[email].password` field — preferred path because it keeps the secret off
# disk. If both are set, the env var wins.
# LEGALOPS_SMTP_PASSWORD=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL — Microsoft 365 / Graph (Outlook ingest)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Azure AD app-registration credentials for the `legalops m365 ...` ingest
# pipeline. Required only if you enable M365 ingest in production.
# LEGALOPS_M365_TENANT_ID=
# LEGALOPS_M365_CLIENT_ID=
# LEGALOPS_M365_CLIENT_SECRET=
# LEGALOPS_M365_USER_PRINCIPAL_NAME=lawyer@firm.example
